comments.body:
Only curators can approve datasets

The approval process includes:
* Mark the DOI as final
* Publish to DataCite the metadata for the dataset 
* Move the files from the pre-curated S3 bucket to the curated S3 bucket.

The dataset becomes read-only once it has been approved.
* You cannot delete a dataset once it has been approved.

We should also remove the "withdraw" button until we figure out the process to deal with changes to datasets once approved.

SPIKE: How do we validate the DataCite record we produce?

comments.body: https://schema.datacite.org/meta/kernel-4.4/metadata.xsd

Schema validation from another project:
https://github.com/pulibrary/lib_jobs/blob/8951eb350389c8cbbf17ff67dc749cdf62d4279b/spec/models/alma_people/alma_person_feed_spec.rb#L92-L99

I found a "data validator" for Datacite, which we can't directly use because it doesn't support Datacite 4.4. However, it's made from code that Kate confirmed could potentially be used to create our own validator for Datacite 4.4. 

**Please see these resources:**

- [Datacite validator](https://format.gbv.de/validate/datacite/xml) for earlier schema; 4.0, 4.1, 4.2
- [GBV/Validation Server](https://github.com/gbv/validation-server#get-validate) possible to make a custom validator

My Questions:
- Would this provide the needed validation?
- Can it be done?
- Would it be too difficult or time-intensive to make a custom validator?

Thanks, hope this helps!
